Implemented only the **“Resting Potential from a Charge Wall”** section changes.

### What I changed

- Updated page title to the requested text in:
  - [src/pages/inspect_resting_potential_charge_wall.ts](/Users/mq20185996/Dropbox/crossleylab/code/electrochemical_signals_progression_web/src/pages/inspect_resting_potential_charge_wall.ts)
  - [src/lessons.json](/Users/mq20185996/Dropbox/crossleylab/code/electrochemical_signals_progression_web/src/lessons.json)

- Fixed Goldman vs membrane-potential consistency in:
  - [src/pages/resting_two_ion_common.ts](/Users/mq20185996/Dropbox/crossleylab/code/electrochemical_signals_progression_web/src/pages/resting_two_ion_common.ts)
  - Changes:
    - Switched to concentration-ratio voltage definitions (`ln(out/in)` form for cations).
    - Corrected Goldman equation direction to `ln((P_Na*Na_out + P_K*K_out)/(P_Na*Na_in + P_K*K_in))`.
    - Made membrane potential trace (`V_total`) use the Goldman form in this two-ion Goldman view so they are consistent.
    - Updated equation text to match this definition.

- Initialized Na and K to equal inside/outside concentrations by default in:
  - [src/pages/resting_two_ion_common.ts](/Users/mq20185996/Dropbox/crossleylab/code/electrochemical_signals_progression_web/src/pages/resting_two_ion_common.ts)
  - Change: `initialLeftFrac` default is now `0.5`.

- Restructured visuals to 3 equal plots in one row in:
  - [src/pages/resting_two_ion_common.ts](/Users/mq20185996/Dropbox/crossleylab/code/electrochemical_signals_progression_web/src/pages/resting_two_ion_common.ts)
  - [src/style.css](/Users/mq20185996/Dropbox/crossleylab/code/electrochemical_signals_progression_web/src/style.css)
  - Changes:
    - Added middle concentration plot (`#concentration-canvas`).
    - Layout now uses `.canvas-grid-3` with three same-size columns:
      1. Particle sim
      2. Na/K concentration plot (inside/outside fractions)
      3. Membrane potential trace + Goldman prediction

### Validation

- Ran build successfully:
